    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bad Connections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Edwin P Berlin letter comments on Christine Rosen's March 20 article deploring how cellphones and TiVo are affecting social mores</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I am not a happy listener when a cellphone conversation is taking place near me. My response is to whip out my billfold, put it to my ear and in a loud voice say: ''Hi, Charlie! I'm calling you on my new wallet-phone combination. It's great! Now I don't have to carry around a separate old-fashioned cellphone that some people are still using.'' Still talking, I hurry away before the phone blabber can ask about it.</p>
        <p>Edwin P. Berlin  San Diego</p>
      </block>
